article.headline: Northern Iowa 76, Florida A&M 53
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Ben Jacobson scored 14 points, Grant Stout added 10 points and 11 rebounds and Northern Iowa shot 11-for-23 from 3-point range to beat Florida A&M 76-53 on Saturday night. UNI (7-1) led by as much as 28 points in picking up its 11th consecutive home win, and fourth straight overall. The Panthers, who never trailed, jumped out to an early 15-4 lead. FAMU (3-5) closed to 16-10, but UNI went on a 14-3 run to push its lead to 30-13 late in the first half. UNI led 37-24 at the break. The Panthers outrebounded the Rattlers 42-28 and forced 18 turnovers. Jacobson shot 4-of-7 from 3-point range. Rome Sanders and Tony Tate each scored 12 for FAMU. Erik Crawford scored nine points, grabbed six rebounds and had out three assists for UNI.
